<doc id="1160468" wikidata="Q5178198" url="?curid=1160468" title="Coursetia">
<text>Coursetia is a genus of flowering plant in the pea family, Fabaceae. Members of the genus, commonly known as babybonnets, are shrubs and small trees native to the Southwestern United States, Mexico, the Caribbean, Central America, and South America as far south as Brazil and Peru. The genus is named for French botanist Georges Louis Marie Dumont de Courset (1746–1824).

==Species==
, Plants of the World Online accepted the following species:

*&quot;Coursetia andina&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia apantensis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia astragalina&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia axillaris&quot; – Texas babybonnets
*&quot;Coursetia barrancana&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia brachyrhachis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia caatingicola&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia cajamarcana&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia caribaea&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia chiapensis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia diversifolia&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia dubia&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia elliptica&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia ferruginea&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia fruticosa&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia glabella&quot; – smooth babybonnets
*&quot;Coursetia glandulosa&quot; – rosary babybonnets
*&quot;Coursetia gracilis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia grandiflora&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia greenmanii&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia guatemalensis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia hassleri&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia hidalgoana&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia hintonii&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia insomniifolia&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia intermontana&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia madrensis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia maraniona&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia mollis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia oaxacensis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia paniculata&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia paucifoliolata&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia planipetiolata&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia polyphylla&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia pumila&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia robinioides&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia rostrata&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia tumbezensis&quot; 
*&quot;Coursetia vicioides&quot; 
